# Wikimyei Config Keys

`src/config/.config` section: `[WIKIMYEI]`

The Wikimyei section binds authored DSL files and grammars into the
graph-first protocol bundle. These paths are part of deterministic protocol
construction; when a component's semantic contract changes, update both its DSL
and BNF path entries.

## Observer Belief

- `wikimyei_observer_belief_dsl_bnf_path`
  - Grammar for `wikimyei.observer.belief.dsl`.
- `wikimyei_observer_belief_dsl_path`
  - Deterministic observer contract that converts Channel MDN NodeLift
    potential distributions into NodeLift-aware allocation belief semantics.
  - V1 requires feature semantics from the Ujcamei kline registry/dock
    coordinate space, base-relative NodeLift projection, arithmetic-return
    scenarios, and a reserve asset supplied as a graph node by `BasePolicy`.
  - The DSL must keep `PROJECTION_VALIDATION_REQUIRED = true` and
    `LIVE_CAPITAL_ALLOWED = false` until projected NodeLift returns have an
    empirical validation artifact.

## Spot Distributional Utility Policy

- `wikimyei_policy_portfolio_spot_distributional_utility_dsl_bnf_path`
  - Grammar for `wikimyei.policy.portfolio.spot_distributional_utility.dsl`.
- `wikimyei_policy_portfolio_spot_distributional_utility_dsl_path`
  - Deterministic portfolio policy contract for the first allocation method.
  - V1 consumes only post-projection `AllocationBelief`, is long-only and
    spot-only, uses projected-gradient search over risky graph-node weights,
    and assigns the residual reserve weight to the reserve graph node.
  - The policy DSL mirrors the observer safety flags:
    `PROJECTION_VALIDATION_REQUIRED = true` and `LIVE_CAPITAL_ALLOWED = false`.

These observer and policy assemblies are included in the graph-first
`wikimyei_registry` and dock-binding report. Lattice can audit their identity
and dock compatibility, but execution authority remains outside Lattice.
